This roster is a listing of all Licensed Child Care and Preschool Programs in the State of Nebraska. It is NOT a listing of Approved (Title XX) Providers. The address shown is the actual location of each Child Care/Preschool Program. The TYPE of Facility is as follows: Provisional or Operating Family Child Care Home I - up to 10 children, one provider, in the provider's home Provisional and Operating Family Child Care Home II - up COMMUNICATIONS COORDINATION & REVIEW CENTER           (updated July 2002)                    The     Center coordinates public communications for USDA general offices, developing     policies and plans for effective execution of development and dissemination of     public affairs information, providing centralized leadership to Department-wide     special information projects, and advising on all aspects of publishing. The     Center develops nationally and internationally significant Departmental news     releases, statements for the media, and similar information prepared in     coordination with other Federal Department or agencies. CCRC counsels and     advises senior officials and agency information directors and staffs in serving     the Department's many audiences, and develops policies and plans for crisis     communications, continuity of OC operations, and for policy regarding     publications, periodicals, and final review of manuscripts. CCRC is responsible     for issuing the employee newsletter, USDA NEWS, and serves as the Departmental     authority for policy and coordination of responses under the Freedom of     Information Act. Women in Agriculture           WIA E-Mail List Service    The Women in Agriculture e-mail list service can provide you with an on-line forum for discussion, exploration, and support. We believe that this e-mail messaging service is an excellent resource for all women worldwide who are involved in agriculture. Subscribers to the list service will receive information, notices, and updates regularly by e-mail.   We urge you, participants of the First and Second International Conferences for Women in Agriculture, and "Ag Women" everywhere to subscribe.      Here's How:   Send an e-mail message to  wialist@rus.usda.gov .  Be sure to include your e-mail address!   Effective June 10, 1999, subscribers to the old Women in Agriculture-Scope list will need to resubscribe to the WIA list using the rus.usda.gov address listed above.  We apologize for the inconvenience.       If you have subscription problems or questions:   Contact the WIA webmaster at  atodd@rdmail.rural.usda.gov.
